om the "am I still on the list" logic to the<br />"WQ_FLAG_WOKEN is set if woken" logic was all well and good, but I<br />missed the case where we did that trylock_page_bit_common().<br /><br />It used to just not add the thing to the list if it would get the page<br />bit, and then the rest of the waiting logic looked at that and was<br />happy.<br /><br />But now if it needs to actually fake that WQ_FLAG_WOKEN flag.<br /><br />So that patch needs to do something like this:<br /><br />        if (!trylock_page_bit_common(page, bit_nr, behavior))<br />                __add_wait_queue_entry_tail(q, wait);<br />        else<br />                wait-&gt;flags |= WQ_FLAG_WOKEN;<br /><br />in there. Or maybe have that bit set originally, and clear it when we<br />add to the wait queue.<br /><br />I'll send a new version after I actually test it.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
